<br>
In my experience, EQ factors in a delay for how far away you are, and even the range on summoned daggers gives you a second or two leeway to turn tail and run.  It just takes practice to learn to pull that way.  Unless of course you are talking about fighting mobs that have a very very large range of attack, in which case pulling with daggers won't help ya much :/.  But otherwise, I never had a problem pulling anywhere with throwing daggers once I got it down pat.  You just have to be in your &quot;fleeing turn&quot; when your throw, not 'throw, turn, run'; but 'turnthrowrun' <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulomack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lomack</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/1/02 4:48:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10879.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: summon item</span><hr size=1> Yes Peregin, your observations are the same as mine and I'm on DSL so I don't think it has anything to do with your connection speed.  However, being able to attack some things at a greater range has its advantages as well.    If you have a hall with multiple agro mobs down its length and you want to &quot;60 single pull&quot; something from down the hall, more range will help you accomplish such without getting close enough to agro other things.<br>
